Please refer to the LICENSE file for license and copyright information.

Please see the INSTALL file for instructions on how to set up and run the tests.

SplunkIt is a performance benchmark kit designed to provide a set of standard
performance measurements for Splunk. It contains an Index Test, which records
various metrics of indexing performance, as well as a Search Test, which
records search times in a test environment that simulates Splunk usage.
After running both tests, you will have a good snapshot of how well Splunk
performs in your specific configuration.

SplunkIt is free software covered under the Apache Software License 2.0.
It also repackages other free open source software.

SplunkIt is unsupported, but do share with us results that you have obtained
and we may post them on our performance blog (blogs.splunk.com/tag/performance).
Please send a screenshot of your SplunkIt Results Summary dashboard to
splunkit@splunk.com along with a description of your hardware configuration.
Also feel free to send questions and feedback to splunkit@splunk.com.


CHANGE HISTORY


SplunkIt version 3.2 (May 2014):

* Added Splunk 6.1 support
* Upgraded to Selenium 2.41.0 which supports up to Firefox 28


SplunkIt version 3.1 (November 2013):

* Python requirements for splunkit-server lowered to 2.6


SplunkIt version 3.0 (October 2013):

* Added Splunk 6 support
* Upgraded to Selenium 33 which gives up to Firefox 21 support
* Added CLI search support


SplunkIt version 2.0 (February 2013):

* Added Splunk 5 support
* Integrated console behavior into the splunkit-server scripts
* Replaced The Grinder with a test framework based on Pyro - no GUI needed
* Removed Apache Ant and Java from system requirements
* Simplified setup of splunkit-user role
* Added the option to use custom scheduled searches and user searches
* Switched from Selenium java client to the Selenium python client
* Upgraded to Selenium 27 (from version 15) and added Firefox 14 support


SplunkIt version 1.0 (April 2012):

* Now compatible with Splunk 4.3
* Added SplunkIt Indexing Details dashboard
* Packaged ant-contrib with SplunkIt in the /thirdparty directory
* New ant "generate-data" target
* New setup ant "setup-splunkit" target
* New ant "gather-results" target to fetch search times from the user machine
* New fields in grinder.properties
* Fixed results dashboard to only show data for the latest SplunkIt run
* Improved the accuracy of the "Time to First Event" search times
* Increased the initial setup time of the Search Test
* Revised the system requirements to include newer versions of firefox
* Added a QUICKSTART file to summarize the install/execution steps
* Upgraded to Grinder 3.6 (from version 3.4)
* Upgraded to Selenium 15 (from version 1.03)

SplunkIt version 0.1 (August 15, 2011):

* Initial Release
